title: 3476 with ASD Error...
message:
Had a 3476 with some issues, no start, no power, then it would start but kernel panic. Replaced corroded r8185 and trace. powered up but kernel panicked.  Ran ASD that failed. Said "ASD-Sensor Failure Voltage VD0R DC-in Failed Value 19.86"
and
Error 2 Sensor reading above alarm point

Any idea what this means?

title: 3476 with ASD Error...
message:
DC In Voltage Sense & Enable (VD0R), page 40.
Check Q5490 area for corrosion.
R5499 open/corroded, or higher value?

title: 3476 with ASD Error...
message: Are you using an 85W charger?? Try a 60W charger... Original of course...
